# ValueLens environment variables
#
# Without a key, ValueLens runs in DEMO MODE using bundled sample data for
# AAPL, MSFT, KO, NVDA, and F — so the app works out of the box.
#
# To enable LIVE data, get a free key at https://financialmodelingprep.com
# and set it here (copy this file to .env.local). The key is used server-side
# only and is never exposed to the browser.

FMP_API_KEY=

# ── Phase 2: accounts (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave these blank to run WITHOUT accounts — auth UI stays hidden and the app
# works exactly like the Phase 1 MVP.
#
# To enable sign-in, watchlists, and saved analyses:
#   1. Create a project at https://supabase.com
#   2. Run db/schema.sql then db/policies.sql in the Supabase SQL editor
#   3. Copy your project URL + anon key from Project Settings → API below
# See db/README.md for the full walkthrough. Both values are safe to expose to
# the browser (the anon key is public by design; RLS protects the data).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
